description: Associates a branch network interface with a trunk network interface. Before you create the association, use CreateNetworkInterface command and set the interface type to trunk. You must also create a network interface for each branch network interface that you want to associate with the trunk network interface.

parameters.name: BranchInterfaceId
parameters.description: The ID of the branch network interface.

parameters.name: TrunkInterfaceId
parameters.description: The ID of the trunk network interface.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description: Unique, case-sensitive identifier that you provide to ensure the idempotency of the request. For more information, see Ensuring idempotency. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

nested_items.name: InterfaceAssociation
nested_items.description: Information about the association between the trunk network interface and branch network interface.

nested_items.name: BranchInterfaceId
nested_items.description: The ID of the branch network interface.

nested_items.name: TrunkInterfaceId
nested_items.description: The ID of the trunk network interface.

nested_items.name: InterfaceProtocol
nested_items.description: The interface protocol. Valid values are VLAN and GRE.

nested_items.name: VlanId
nested_items.description: The ID of the VLAN when you use the VLAN protocol.

nested_items.name: GreKey
nested_items.description: The application key when you use the GRE protocol.

nested_items.name: Tags
nested_items.description: The tags for the trunk interface association.

nested_items.name: ClientToken
nested_items.description: Unique, case-sensitive identifier that you provide to ensure the idempotency of the request. For more information, see Ensuring idempotency.
